{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17657062","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17657062"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:22:23+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:22:23+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19093"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"19093","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/19093"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.15,0.75,0.05,0.05,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11827"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"81207"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11827","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11827"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19093"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66540"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"44"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"976"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4943"},{"type":"tags","id":"5221"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27781"},{"type":"contributions","id":"29650"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"81207","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/81207"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following opioids has the highest potency relative to morphine?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Codeine","Fentanyl","Oxycodone","Hydromorphone","Tramadol"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe relative potency of opioids compared to morphine varies significantly. \u003Cstrong\u003EFentanyl\u003C/strong\u003E is approximately 100 times more potent than morphine, making it the most potent of the listed options.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe relative potencies of the other options compared to morphine are:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECodeine\u003C/strong\u003E is approximately 0.1 times as potent as morphine\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EOxycodone\u003C/strong\u003E is approximately 1.5 times as potent as morphine\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHydromorphone\u003C/strong\u003E is approximately 5 times as potent as morphine\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETramadol\u003C/strong\u003E is approximately 0.1 times as potent as morphine\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThese potency ratios are important when converting between different opioids. Due to incomplete cross-tolerance between opioids, when converting between different agents, it is recommended to reduce the calculated equianalgesic dose by 25-50% initially for safety.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Fentanyl is approximately 100 times more potent than morphine in equianalgesic dosing.","Understanding relative opioid potencies is crucial for safe opioid rotation and conversion.","Different opioids have varying potencies due to their receptor binding affinities and pharmacokinetic properties."],"references":["ANZCA Faculty of Pain Medicine, Opioid Dose Equivalence Calculation Table, 2021, https://www.anzca.edu.au/getattachment/6892fb13-47fc-446b-a7a2-11cdfe1c9902/PS01(PM)-(Appendix)-Opioid-Dose-Equivalence-Calculation-Table"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66540"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19093"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66540","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/66540"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-25T07:15:45+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-2